{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/education/universities","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"Universities","meta_description":"In-person attendance of university students in schools is banned. ","content":{"processed":"<h2><strong>Rules and recommendations </strong></h2>\n<p><strong>In-person attendance of university students in schools is banned except for a few exceptions. </strong></p>\n<p>In-person attendance in clinical, practical tuition and praxis that take place at external subjects are allowed. In-person <strong>attendance of up to 20 students</strong> in laboratory, experimental or artistic tuition for students of the <strong>last year of bachelor's and master's degree study program is also permitted</strong>. An exception also includes students with a doctoral degrees. Clinical and practical tuition of <strong>medical disciplines </strong>and <strong>pedagogical praxis </strong>in preschool, elementary and high schools also have an exception.   </p>\n<p><strong>In-person attendance at exams is permitted assuming that a</strong>t one time are up to 10 persons present. Specific exams of medical professions have an exception from this prohibition.  </p>\n<p><strong>Individual consultations and individual visits of libraries </strong>for the purpose of obtaining or handing out study literature are permitted. </p>\n<p>It is important to follow the <strong>attitudes of a particular university</strong>, because rectors may make their own decisions. A good source of information is particular<strong> websites of each university</strong> and their <strong>students' affairs offices</strong>. Besides that, you may also contact f.e. the <strong>Academical senate.</strong> </p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/education/universities"},"changed":"2020-12-20T23:03:54+00:00","valid_from":"2020-11-02T00:00:00+01:00","langcode":"en","created":"2020-11-06T14:40:07+00:00","links":[{"uri":"https://www.msmt.cz/aktualni-opatreni-pro-vysoke-skoly-v-souvislosti-s-covid-19","title":"The Ministry  of Education: current information regarding universities"}],"relationships":{"region":[{"name":"All regions of Czechia"}],"icon":{"code":"school"},"situation_type":{"name":"Education","path":{"alias":"/situations/education"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"school"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Higher Vocational Schools","path":{"alias":"/situations/education/higher-vocational-schools","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Distance learning","path":{"alias":"/situations/education/distance-learning","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"Students' work duty","path":{"alias":"/situations/education/students-work-duty","langcode":"en"}},{"title":"School accommodation facilities","path":{"alias":"/situations/household-and-housing/school-accommodation-facilities","langcode":"en"}}]},"questions_answers":[],"update":{"processed":"<p>Od 4.1. se omezuje výuka na vysokých školách. Výjimkou jsou zkoušky maximálně v počtu 10 osob a účast na klinické a praktické výuce a praxi studentů studijních programů všeobecné lékařství, zubní lékařství, farmacie a dalších zdravotnických studijních programů a studentů vykonávajících pedagogickou praktickou výuku a praxi v mateřských, základních a středních školách nebo školských zařízeních pro výkon ústavní a ochranné výchovy.</p>\n","valid_from":"2021-01-04T00:00:00+01:00","pes":"5"},"valid_to":null,"last_updated":"2020-12-20T15:40:07+01:00"},"situationArea":{"name":"Education","path":{"alias":"/situations/education"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"school"},"situation":[{"id":"3dd749d6-d2da-52f3-88a2-4d741d585785","title":"Kindergartens","path":{"alias":"/situations/education/kindergartens"}},{"id":"3ab3376a-a24a-5ff4-9699-1e8976dca5a7","title":"Primary schools","path":{"alias":"/situations/education/primary-schools"}},{"id":"c7139802-0cf5-521a-8a72-b99b25003344","title":"Secondary schools","path":{"alias":"/situations/education/secondary-schools"}},{"id":"fe9f43